        <briefdescription>
<para>Perform a write-then-read I2C transaction. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sends a START, writes the device address + tx_data, then issues a repeated START, reads rx_len bytes into rx_data, and sends a STOP. This covers the common &quot;write register address, read data&quot; pattern.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>i2c</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>I2C instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev_addr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>7-bit device address (will be left-shifted internally). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>tx_data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Data to write (e.g., register address). Can be NULL if tx_len is 0. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>tx_len</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of bytes to write. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rx_data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Buffer to read into. Can be NULL if rx_len is 0. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rx_len</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of bytes to read. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>true if all bytes were ACKed, false on NACK. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
